# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version is
#   controlled by the user.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1255, lock files are meant to be committed,
#   but if you prefer to keep your environment strictly local, you can ignore them.
#   However, for applications, you should definitely commit your Pipfile.lock.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it's generally recommended to commit poetry.lock.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
